<%- include('partials/head') %>
<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="hero-header">
    <div class="background parallax" style="background-image: url('/img/trees.jpg')"></div>
    <div class="logo-block"><%- include('assets/logo.svg') %></div>
    <a class="scroll-hint -hidden" href="#top" data-no-url>Scroll down</a>
</div>

<div id="top"><%- include('partials/menu') %></div>

<main itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Katy Holvey Proofrerading">
    <meta itemprop="image" content="/img/logo.svg">
    <meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://katyholvey.co.uk">

    <section class="intro -medium">
        <div class="container">
            <div>
                <h1>Comprehensive<br>proofreading services</h1>
                <div itemprop="description">
                    <p>I am a freelance proofreader with a background in natural history and wildlife conservation.</p>
                    <p>Whether you are a publisher, self-publisher, business, charity, blog writer, or student, I provide a meticulous, high quality service. By detecting and correcting errors in your writing and layout I can give your work a professional and polished look so that your readers can really focus on the content of your text.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <a class="cta-button" href="#contact">Get a quote now</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bio -medium">
        <div id="about" class="scroll-offset"></div> 
        <div class="container">
            <img src="/img/katy.jpg" alt="Photo of Katy">
            <div>
                <p>I am passionate about words and the English language and I always have my nose in a book. After originally graduating with a degree in Zoology, my main focus is now on language and how it works. Grammar, spelling, and punctuation are my watchwords!</p>
                <a class="cta-button -light" href="about">Read more</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about -light">
        <div class="container">
            <div>
                <h1>What is proofreading?</h1>
                <p>Proofreading is the art of reading a document or publication to detect and correct errors in the text. These errors may be simple typos, grammatical mistakes, or problems with the way text is laid out on a page.</p>
                <p>I provide a range of proofreading services, from a basic check to a comprehensive proofread.</p>
                <a class="cta-button" href="#services">See all services</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section-image -right"><img src="/img/type.jpg" alt></div>
    </section>

    <section class="quote -dark -slim -small">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="symbol-group"><%- include('assets/symbols.svg') %></div>
            <div>
                <h1>What are those marks?</h1>
                <p>The British Standards Institution (BSI) proof-correction symbols are used both in Britain and internationally. These BSI symbols are added to an electronic or paper document by a proofreader or editor to indicate and correct problems in a text.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="services -medium" itemprop="makesOffer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Offer">
        <div id="services" class="scroll-offset"></div>
        <div itemprop="itemOffered" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Service">
            <div itemprop="serviceOutput" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Thing">
                <meta itemprop="name" content="Proofreading">
                <meta itemprop="identifier" content="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proofreading">
            </div>
            <div itemprop="areaServed" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Country">
                <meta itemprop="identifier" content="United Kingdom">
            </div>

            <div class="container">
                <div itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Offer">
                    <h1 itemprop="name">Proofreading for any budget</h1>
                    <p><span itemprop="description">I provide a versatile proofreading service, starting from a basic check of your text for grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors to a full proofread of your document, and anything in between.</span> This can include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>checking your text for grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors;</li>
                        <li>checking your text for consistency in spacing, layout, and alignment (for example, checking spacing before and after paragraphs and headings);</li>
                        <li>checking your text for consistency of heading styles, paragraph styles, list styles, and fonts;</li>
                        <li>checking displayed materials (such as illustrations, graphs, and tables) for grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors;</li>
                        <li>checking displayed materials for consistency in spacing, layout, alignment and positioning;</li>
                        <li>checking displayed materials for consistency within and between them (for example, checking that captions are consistent in style and layout and match the material they are attached to);</li>
                        <li>checking notes, references, and bibliographies for grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors;</li>
                        <li>checking notes, references, and bibliographies for consistency in style, spacing and layout.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>I make corrections where things are wrong but I won't make changes if theyâ€™re not needed. I will note queries for anything in your document that needs clarification.</p>
                    <p>I can mark up your work onscreen in Adobe Reader using either BSI symbols or Comment tools, or in Microsoft Word using Track Changes. If you prefer dealing with hard copies I can mark up on paper using BSI symbols.</p>
                    <p>Note for students: Although most universities allow a professional proofreader to check your work, you should consult your university's guidelines on proofreading before contacting me.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact -light">
        <div id="contact" class="scroll-offset"></div>
        <div class="container">
            <div>
                <h1>Get in touch or request a quote</h1>
                <p>Have questions or want to find out what I can do for your project? Just send me a message and I'll be in touch.</p>
                <form class="contact-form">
                    <main>
                        <div class="form-field">
                            <label for="contact-form-name">Name</label>
                            <input type="text" required name="name" id="contact-form-name" placeholder="your name">
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-field">
                            <label for="contact-form-phone">Phone</label>
                            <input type="phone" name="phone" id="contact-form-phone" placeholder="your phone number">
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-field">
                            <label for="contact-form-email">Email</label>
                            <input type="email" required name="email" id="contact-form-email" placeholder="your email address">
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-field">
                            <label for="contact-form-message">How can I help?</label>
                            <textarea required name="message" id="contact-form-message"></textarea>
                        </div>
                    </main>
                    <footer>
                        <div class="file-upload">
                            <%- include('./assets/icon-document.svg') %>
                            <div>
                                <div class="info -default">Document to upload?</div>
                                <div class="info -count" data-count="0"> file<span class="plural">s</span> added</div>
                                <label for="contact-form-files" tabindex="0">Choose a file</label> or drag it here
                            </div>
                            <input type="file" name="files[]" id="contact-form-files" multiple>
                        </div>
                        <button type="submit" class="cta-button">
                            <span class="label">Send message</span>
                            <span class="busy">Sending</span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="status">
                            <p class="success">Your message has been sent</p>
                            <p class="error">Something went wrong. Please try again</p>
                        </div>
                    </footer>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<%- include('partials/tail') %>
